# SwarmTrade — Cursor Rules

## READ FIRST
You are building a multi-agent AI committee system for autonomous cryptocurrency paper trading.
Before writing any code, read ARCHITECTURE.md for the full system design, schema, and agent specifications.

---

## What This System Does

Six specialist AI agents (Bull, Bear, Quant, Macro, Sentiment, Risk Management) deliberate on
incoming trade signals from TradingView. A central Orchestrator agent synthesises their analysis
into a final trade decision. All trades execute in paper (simulated) mode via OctoBot during
validation. No real capital is deployed until strict performance criteria are met.

---

## Stack — Use Only These Technologies

- **Runtime:** Node.js
- **Hosting:** Railway (Docker, GitHub integration)
- **Database:** Supabase (PostgreSQL + real-time subscriptions)
- **Trade execution:** OctoBot (open source, Docker, paper trading mode)
- **LLMs:** Anthropic API only — do not suggest OpenAI or other providers
- **Agent models:** Defined in /config/models.js — never hardcode model strings elsewhere
- **Risk Agent:** Deterministic rules engine — absolutely no LLM
- **Dashboard:** React, Railway hosted, Supabase real-time subscriptions
- **Do not introduce** any framework, library, or service not listed in ARCHITECTURE.md without flagging it first

---

## MODEL ROUTING — READ BEFORE EVERY TASK

### The Golden Rule
All Anthropic model strings are defined in /config/models.js only.
Never write a model string anywhere else in the codebase.
Always import from /config/models.js in agent files.

### Correct import pattern — use this every time
```javascript
const { MODELS, TOKEN_BUDGETS } = require('../../config/models.js');

const response = await anthropic.messages.create({
  model:      MODELS.bull,         // ← always from config, never inline
  max_tokens: TOKEN_BUDGETS.bull,  // ← always from config, never inline
  messages:   [{ role: 'user', content: prompt }],
});
```

### Model assignments (reference only — config/models.js is authoritative)
| Agent | Model | Cursor session model |
|---|---|---|
| Orchestrator | claude-sonnet-4-5 | Use Sonnet in Cursor |
| Macro | claude-sonnet-4-5 | Use Sonnet in Cursor |
| Bull | claude-haiku-4-5-20251001 | Haiku sufficient in Cursor |
| Bear | claude-haiku-4-5-20251001 | Haiku sufficient in Cursor |
| Sentiment | claude-haiku-4-5-20251001 | Haiku sufficient in Cursor |
| Quant | claude-haiku-4-5-20251001 | Haiku sufficient in Cursor |
| Risk | NO MODEL | No Anthropic calls ever |

### Session reminders — say this at the start of each task

When starting work on Orchestrator or Macro code, say:
> "This component uses claude-sonnet-4-5. Please ensure Sonnet is selected in the
> Cursor model dropdown before we proceed. Working with the wrong model here will
> reduce synthesis quality."

When starting work on Bull, Bear, Sentiment, or Quant code, say:
> "This component uses claude-haiku-4-5-20251001. If you have Sonnet selected in
> Cursor you can switch down to Haiku to reduce cost — the task does not require
> Sonnet-level reasoning."

When starting work on Risk Agent code, say:
> "Risk Agent is a deterministic rules engine. Zero LLM calls. Zero Anthropic imports.
> Proceeding with pure logic only. Flag immediately if any Anthropic reference appears."

### Violation flags — treat these as bugs, not warnings
- Model string hardcoded anywhere other than /config/models.js → BUG
- Any Anthropic import or API call inside /agents/risk/ → CRITICAL BUG
- max_tokens set inline rather than from TOKEN_BUDGETS → BUG
- Agent response not validated against AGENT_OUTPUT_SCHEMA before Supabase write → BUG

