## Current Build Phase

**PHASE 1 — FOUNDATION**

Build only what is listed here. Do not build Phase 2 features until Phase 1 is stable.

- [ ] /config/models.js created and imported correctly in at least one agent as proof of pattern
- [ ] OctoBot deployed on Railway via Docker in paper trading mode
- [ ] TradingView webhook handler live and receiving alerts
- [ ] Supabase migrations for all four tables created and applied
- [ ] Signals logging to Supabase on receipt
- [ ] Basic Risk Agent (rules engine, no LLM) operational
- [ ] Basic Quant Agent (deterministic calculations) operational
- [ ] Paper trades logging to Supabase

Phase 2 begins when all Phase 1 checkboxes are complete and signals are logging correctly for 48+ hours.

---

## Code Style

- Async/await throughout — no raw Promise chains
- Every Supabase write wrapped in try/catch with error logged to console
- Agent functions must be pure where possible — inputs in, structured output out
- Validate every agent response against AGENT_OUTPUT_SCHEMA from /config/models.js before writing to Supabase
- No global state outside of Supabase — treat the database as the single source of truth
- Comment any non-obvious logic, especially in the deliberation flow and risk rules
- Keep agent prompt templates in separate prompt.js files — not inline strings
- Model strings and token budgets always from /config/models.js — never inline

---

## When in Doubt

1. Check ARCHITECTURE.md before making a structural decision
2. Check /config/models.js before writing any Anthropic API call
3. If a rule above conflicts with something that seems like a good idea, follow the rule and flag the conflict
4. If adding a new dependency, state why and wait for confirmation before installing
5. Never delete or modify existing Supabase migration files — only add new ones
6. If you see a hardcoded model string outside of /config/models.js, stop and fix it before continuing
